# sparklogs-redact lockstep versioning

Read repo root [README.md](../../README.md) **Versioning** section first.

## Rules

1. **Never bump one package alone** — `@sparklogs/redact-core`, `@sparklogs/redact-cli`, and
   `@sparklogs/redact-react` share the same semver in `package.json`.
2. **`@sparklogs/redact-core` range** — in `redact-cli` and `redact-react`, set
   `"@sparklogs/redact-core": "^X.Y.Z"` where `X.Y.Z` is that shared version.
3. **Changelogs** — all three `packages/*/CHANGELOG.md` must exist. Either all have `## Unreleased`
   or none do. Latest `## X.Y.Z` heading must match `package.json`. Put `## Unreleased` above release
   sections.
4. **Dev PRs** — edit `## Unreleased` only in packages you changed; keep `package.json` at the current
   release until a release PR.
5. **Release PR** — bump all versions, promote `## Unreleased` → `## X.Y.Z` in every changelog (stub
   line for packages with no functional change), run `npm install` at repo root, then
   `make check-versions`.

## Verify

```bash
make check-versions
```

Implemented in [`scripts/check-lockstep-versions.mjs`](../../scripts/check-lockstep-versions.mjs); wired into `make ci`.
